# Performance / Core Web Vitals

Protect **LCP · INP · CLS** on home, PLP, PDP, cart, checkout.

## Practical budgets

| Surface | Rule |
|---|---|
| LCP hero | One `next/image` with `priority`; don’t start it at `opacity: 0` waiting on GSAP |
| Checkout / cart | Minimal third-party JS; **no** heavy GSAP import on pay path |
| Lists | Prefer Server Components; client islands only for interactivity |

Measure before micro-optimizing. Prefer **deleting JS** over clever tweaks.

## Do

```tsx
// LCP hero only
<Image src={hero} alt="…" priority sizes="100vw" className="…" />

// Below-fold — default lazy; reserve space
<div className="relative aspect-[4/5]">
  <Image src={url} alt={name} fill sizes="(max-width:768px) 50vw, 25vw" />
</div>
```

- Cache public catalog HTML carefully; **never** cache private cart/account responses.
- Dynamic-import GSAP scenes when they hurt LCP.

## Don't

- Unsized images / banners that shift layout (CLS)
- Huge client carousels on first paint
- Blocking third-party scripts on checkout
- Animating layout props when transform/opacity work
